        {
            "name": "Requirements",
            "blockname": "PrePlacement Info",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Requirements",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "The placement will have various requirements. It is useful for students to be aware of these requirements before starting the placement. They can find details about the requirements through reading their placement handbook and the competencies. They can also direct any questions about these requirements to their personal tutor, learning support tutor or course leader well before the placement begins.",
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Placement providers are expected to give the student an induction to the organisation, typically this will happen on the first day of placement. At induction, it is appropriate to provide students with"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "list-text",
                            "list_elements": [
                                {
                                    "text": "an overview of the organisational structure"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "relevant health and safety policies"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "training in the use of equipment and systems the student will use"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "provide information on risks in the environment, particularly discuss potential risks and mitigations with students who have disabilities"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "a set of clear aims and objectives for the student"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Guidance on how the student can provide feedback to their educator or mentor"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Structured meetings to monitor the progress of a students and opportunity to raise any concerns"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "It is the responsibility of the placement provider to integrate students into the organisation, plans and relevant partners. Placement teams at the University will explain your role in the assessment of students."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Student preparation",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Students have been adequately briefed prior to starting their placement, each student will have a handbook and appropriate information about the placement. The student should be aware of"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "list-text",
                            "list_elements": [
                                {
                                    "text": "General health and safety issues"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "their responsibilities and expected behaviour during placement"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "what will be expected of them by the University and regulatory bodies when undertaking a placement"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "assessment processes"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Health and safety",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "The University has a duty of care to students on placements, making sure that they are working in suitable learning environments which meet health and safety standards. Placement providers re expected to inform students of any potential risks in the workplace and make sure they receive adequate training, induction and supervision. Students are expected to be honest and transparent about their skills and scope of practice, demonstrating a willingness to learn the required skills and be assessed when appropriate."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "University â€“ Placement Liaison",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Placement teams will be in contact with placement providers to ensure the student is getting on well.. Students may have visits from a tutor to monitor their progress and discuss any concerns."
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "blockname": "PrePlacement Info",
            "name": "PrePlacement Visit",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Students may need a pre-placement visit.",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Some students may need a pre-placement visit this could be facilitated by the Learning Support Tutor in collaboration with the placement team."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "It is the studentâ€™s responsibility to prepare for a pre placement visit. Learning Support Tutors and the disability team have support mechanisms in place to support students who are organising a pre placement visit and empower them to articulate their need and think about reasonable adjustments.",
                            "space_after": true
                        },
